  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The quasi Jewish center, as we would call it in English, was really not to service or enhance Jewish life, but was to serve the Germans with a documentation as to the residents, the occupation, or whatever Jews might be doing.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, you see, in Germany we had a system, a police system, a police state that is not known United States.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Number one, in order to be able to live in a city, Gentiles and Jews alike had to register with the police.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So Germans always knew where everybody was-- by address, by location, or by workplace.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Number two, if you wanted to go to vacation somewhere-- you wanted to visit your grandparents-- if it was more than one week, you had to de-register in the city where you live and re-register in the city you were visiting.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the Germans knew where everybody was every minute of the day-- or every day that they were I guess you might say at home, unless it was a less than seven day vacation trip.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Jewish center had the responsibility of doing the same thing that the police did.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had to know where everybody was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And with this particular facility that we had to go and pick up the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, you hear both by rumors and by connections that you did keep with your friends and your families.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because you were interested all this time to leave the country, to leave Germany, to emigrate to any country in the world that would have you, you kept in touch with the Jewish center because they provided information as to where you might have entry and how to get there.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But most of the time, of course, it was your own individual effort to try to escape Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
